# COMPUTE THE FRACTION OF DATA REMAINING AFTER NAN REMOVAL 

# INSERT CODE

df= sns.load_dataset("titanic", cache=True)

Nrows_original = df.shape[0]
Ncols_original = df.shape[1]
matrix_entries_original = Nrows_original * Ncols_original

df_cleaned = df_processed.dropna()

Nrows_cleaned = df_cleaned.shape[0]
Ncols_cleaned = df_cleaned.shape[1]
matrix_entries_cleaned = Nrows_cleaned * Ncols_cleaned

percentage_remaining = (matrix_entries_cleaned / matrix_entries_original) * 100

print(f"ORIGINAL\nNrows =  {Nrows_original}\nNcol= {Ncols_original}\nMatrix entries =  {matrix_entries_original}")

print(f"\nNAN REMOVED\nNrows =  {Nrows_cleaned}\nNcol= {Ncols_cleaned}\nMatrix entries =  {matrix_entries_cleaned}")
print(f"Percentage remaining: {percentage_remaining:.6f}")

correlation_matrix = df_cleaned[['survived', 'pclass', 'age', 'sibsp', 'parch', 'fare', 'adult_male', 'alone']].corr()

print("------------------------")
print("PEARSON CORRELATION MATRIX:")
print("------------------------")
print(correlation_matrix.round(6))

mask = np.triu(np.ones_like(correlation_matrix, dtype=bool))
plt.rcParams.update({'font.size': 10})
heatmap = sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, 
                      annot=False,
                      mask=mask, 
                      cmap="coolwarm", 
                      vmin=-0.6, vmax=0.2, 
                      center=0,
